# General Focus Upgrades
##############################
focus.upgrade.potency.nam=Potency
focus.upgrade.potency.tex=This upgrade increases the damage or strength of the focus's powers. The exact damage increase varies from focus to focus, but is usually about 20% per level.
focus.upgrade.frugal.nam=Frugal
focus.upgrade.frugal.tex=This upgrade reduces the vis cost of activating the focus's powers by 10% per level.
focus.upgrade.treasure.nam=Treasure
focus.upgrade.treasure.tex=This upgrade acts like the Fortune or Looting enchantments. It increases the chance of getting more/better loot.
focus.upgrade.enlarge.nam=Enlarge
focus.upgrade.enlarge.tex=This upgrade increases how large an area the focus's powers effect, or increases the number of targets effected.
focus.upgrade.extend.nam=Extend
focus.upgrade.extend.tex=This upgrade increases the duration of any effects the upgrade might create.
focus.upgrade.architect.nam=Architect
focus.upgrade.architect.tex=This upgrade gives a lot more control over the area certain foci effect. The exact area that will be effected is displayed and you can change the size using the misc wand toggle key (default G). Sneak+G allows you to toggle which dimensions you can change.
#
# Specific Focus Upgrades
##############################
focus.upgrade.chainlightning.nam=Chain Lightning
focus.upgrade.chainlightning.tex=This upgrade reduces the speed at which the focus fires bolts, but the damage is increased and the bolt can chain to up to two additional targets.
focus.upgrade.earthshock.nam=Earth Shock
focus.upgrade.earthshock.tex=Instead of a bolt of lightning, the focus now lobs a ball of electrical energy. It inflicts damage in an area around where it hits and leaves the ground dangerously electrified for some time.
focus.upgrade.fireball.nam=Fireball
focus.upgrade.fireball.tex=The focus will now produce a explosive ball of fire you can hurl at your foes. The Alchemists Fire upgrade causes it to also set the ground aflame around the point of impact.
focus.upgrade.firebeam.nam=Fire Beam
focus.upgrade.firebeam.tex=The focus now emits a narrow stream of fire instead of a wide swathe. It burns through anything it touches inflicting massive damage.
focus.upgrade.batbombs.nam=Bat Bombs
focus.upgrade.batbombs.tex=This upgrade will make the summoned firebats even more volatile. They always explode when they contact their target and the explosion will be a lot more potent than normal.
focus.upgrade.devilbats.nam=Devil Bats
focus.upgrade.devilbats.tex=With this upgrade applied the summoned bats are larger, tougher and nastier. They will never explode, but keep attacking their target till it expires or they are slain. 
focus.upgrade.vampirebats.nam=Vampire Bats
focus.upgrade.vampirebats.tex=This upgrade changes the summoned bats into vampire bats. Not only will they suck the life out of their target to replenish their own, but some of the stolen life force is given to their summoner.
focus.upgrade.scattershot.nam=Scattershot
focus.upgrade.scattershot.tex=Instead of a single shard of ice, the focus will now fire multiple shards. Each shard does minimal damage, but a concentrated volley of them can do significant damage to a single target. 
focus.upgrade.iceboulder.nam=Ice Boulder
focus.upgrade.iceboulder.tex=The focus will now create a large boulder of ice. The boulder has a tendancy to bounce around making it deadly in skilled hands. 
focus.upgrade.alchemistsfire.nam=Alchemist's Fire
focus.upgrade.alchemistsfire.tex=This increases the potency of the elemental fire in the focus. Any targets set alight will burn for much longer.
focus.upgrade.alchemistsfrost.nam=Alchemist's Frost
focus.upgrade.alchemistsfrost.tex=This increases the potency of the elemental cold in the focus. When the focus targets or damages a creature it will be chilled and slowed significantly.
focus.upgrade.nightshade.nam=Nightshade
focus.upgrade.nightshade.tex=Normally the Pech's curse focus inflicts one of a small handful of debilitating effects. With this upgrade it will inflict all of them at once.
focus.upgrade.silktouch.nam=Silk Touch
focus.upgrade.silktouch.tex=Like the enchantment of the same name, this upgrade allows you to pick up harvested blocks as-is instead of gaining the normal drops.
focus.upgrade.seeker.nam=Seeker
focus.upgrade.seeker.tex=This upgrade makes the orbs created by the primal focus seek out the nearest living target and not wander all over the place. This makes them a lot more stable which also means they won't do anything unusual beyond exploding.
focus.upgrade.dowsing.nam=Dowsing
focus.upgrade.dowsing.tex=This upgrade gives the excavation focus a small chance to mine native clusters instead of normal ores. These clusters usually give double the number of ingots when smelted.
focus.upgrade.persistant.nam=Persistant
focus.upgrade.persistant.tex=When the target if this focus dies, disappears or moves out of range, the missile will seek another target of the same type nearby.
focus.upgrade.sticky.nam=Sticky
focus.upgrade.sticky.tex=The grapple does not automatically detach when you get close enough - you must manually detach from it. 
